1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:07,170
-How is my father's condition?
-If he keeps pushing himself, at this rate he will suffer a myocardial infarction.

2
00:00:07,170 --> 00:00:11,960
I'll do it. I'm going to protect his company.

3
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:14,430
If Irie-kun is feeling uneasy and needs help...

4
00:00:14,430 --> 00:00:19,810
If there is something that I can do, I would do anything.

5
00:00:19,810 --> 00:00:23,580
At this rate, Pandai may have to undergo a merger.

6
00:00:23,580 --> 00:00:26,450
We need an enormous amount of financial support immediately.

7
00:00:26,450 --> 00:00:30,260
This is Hokueisha's Chairman Oizumi
and his secretary, Mr. Yokoyama.

8
00:00:30,290 --> 00:00:32,820
On behalf of my father

9
00:00:32,820 --> 00:00:35,250
I would like to discuss the investment plan with you.

10
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:40,840
My father is actually not doing well.

11
00:00:42,330 --> 00:00:45,170
If I take over the company,
all of the problems will be solved.

12
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:58,270
I'm delighted that you paid us
a visit at our company, Chairman.

13
00:00:58,270 --> 00:01:01,130
-Thank you very much for coming.
-Well, well...

14
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:05,010
I had something to do in this area today.

15
00:01:05,010 --> 00:01:07,460
Are by alone today?

16
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,580
I came here to talk to you
about a personal matter, Naoki-kun.

17
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:15,140
Talk to me?

18
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:20,490
Naoki-kun, would you like to have
an arranged marriage meeting?

19
00:01:26,180 --> 00:01:29,630
I know it's not the best time
since Mr. Irie is in the hospital...

20
00:01:29,630 --> 00:01:32,670
I have a granddaughter.

21
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:37,600
She is your age and goes to
Seishin Women's College.

22
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:40,560
It's a really prestigious school.

23
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:43,050
What do you think, Naoki-kun?

24
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:47,280
Would you at least like to meet her?

25
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:52,950
You are young.

26
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:55,380
I'm sure you need time
to think about it.

27
00:01:55,420 --> 00:02:01,450
After discussing it with your parents
please give me your answer in the next few days.

28
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:08,680
We will talk about the
investment plan afterward.

29
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:11,810
I'm sorry for visiting you
without notice.

30
00:02:11,810 --> 00:02:14,100
Please don't apologize.

31
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:20,350
Well then, Naoki-kun.
Please consider this carefully.

32
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:21,600
Yes.

33
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,840
Thank you very much.

34
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:34,190
Naoki-san.

35
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:37,320
This meeting is...

36
00:02:37,380 --> 00:02:41,720
going to be a great advantage
for the company, isn't it?

37
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:46,500
What is this all about, Naoki?

38
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,580
Wait, Honey. Calm down.

39
00:02:49,580 --> 00:02:54,510
However, out of the blue you're having
an arranged marriage meeting with...

40
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:58,240
The Chairman's granddaughter?
-What is going on?

41
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:01,090
Nothing.

42
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:04,010
Don't tell me that...

43
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:07,330
you are doing this for the financial support?

44
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:16,570
We didn't tell them that we were coming.
Don't you think Daddy will be surprised?

45
00:03:16,570 --> 00:03:19,420
What should we do?
It might be bad for his heart if we surprise him.

46
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:20,880
What are you talking about?

47
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:25,310
If he sees Yuki-kun's face,
he will get better right away!

48
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:29,580
Don't underestimate us!

49
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:38,010
I don't want to protect my company
by sacrificing your life.

50
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:41,890
He's right. Marriage? I won't allow this.

51
00:03:41,890 --> 00:03:43,420
"Marriage?"

52
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:45,650
Naoki is?

53
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:52,510
I'm proud of myself for building Pandai
this big in just one generation.

54
00:03:52,510 --> 00:03:55,410
So don't take us the wrong way.

55
00:03:56,530 --> 00:04:01,430
You have to marry
someone that you really love.

56
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:07,260
I like her.

57
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,490
I saw her in a picture.

58
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:16,060
She was my type.

59
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,970
Naoki!!

60
00:04:17,970 --> 00:04:20,530
-Are you serious?
-Yuki!

61
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:23,620
Are you really getting married?
But...

62
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:27,540
Kotoko-chan. You are here too, Mr. Aihara.

63
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,250
Irie-kun.

64
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:43,360
Is it true that you're going to
have an arranged marriage meeting?

65
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:46,950
Yes.

66
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:51,670
This coming Sunday.

67
00:04:51,670 --> 00:04:54,130
Since my father is not doing well,

68
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:58,670
we are going to have a casual meeting.

69
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:04,980
I need you to come with me, Mom.

70
00:05:05,030 --> 00:05:07,540
Please.

71
00:05:24,770 --> 00:05:26,290
Oh no...

72
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:29,430
Irie-kun is going to have an
arranged marriage meeting...

73
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:32,220
I can't believe this.

74
00:05:33,210 --> 00:05:35,560
What am I...

75
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:38,170
supposed to do?

76
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:45,400
♫  Have you noticed?
I keep updating myself ♫

77
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:50,500
♫ Hopefully, I'll reach you someday ♫

78
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:04,910
♫ Where are your true feelings? ♫

79
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:11,260
♫ To think that you can neither avoid nor love me,
Isn't that boring? ♫

80
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:16,280
♫ I thought about this many times ♫

81
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:22,100
♫ Please share it with me, even only half is fine ♫

82
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:27,750
♫ Rather than counting the efforts that surely won't be rewarded ♫

83
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:33,750
♫ if you make up tomorrow's strategy,
Now go for it ♫

84
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:39,850
♫ Make an update,
I can't understand these days full of mischief ♫

85
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:45,200
♫ But I still like them a lot ♫

86
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:51,250
♫ Notice me, I always keep updating myself ♫

87
00:06:51,270 --> 00:07:00,630
♫ Hopefully, I'll reach you someday ♫

88
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:06,890
♫  Have you noticed?
I keep updating myself ♫

89
00:07:06,910 --> 00:07:12,410
♫ I can't stop worrying about little things,
but I really want to catch up with you ♫

90
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:18,270
♫ I want to go on a date with you soon,
and hope that we might be the best couple someday ♫

91
00:07:18,290 --> 00:07:23,690
♫ I can't understand all of this mischief,
but I still like it a lot ♫

92
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:29,840
♫ Notice me, I always keep updating myself ♫

93
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:35,000
♫ Hopefully, I'll reach you someday ♫

94
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:43,400
[Mischievous Kiss]
[Love in Tokyo]

95
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:46,830
That punk Irie is going to have
an arranged marriage meeting?

96
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:50,010
[Episode 14: A Fork in the Path of Love]
The other person is the granddaughter
of their business partner.

97
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:52,840
That's like a marriage of convenience!

98
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:55,040
Does that still happen nowadays?

99
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,980
I don't know.

100
00:07:56,980 --> 00:08:01,360
Irie-kun said he liked the girl.

101
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:06,190
I'm sorry, but I should go.

102
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,430
Oh, do you think Kotoko is okay?

103
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:13,220
There is no way that she is okay.

104
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:17,310
Don't you know how many years
she had a crush on Irie?

105
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:18,800
You are right.

106
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:22,020
But I didn't think that damn Irie would have
an arranged marriage meeting.

107
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:24,050
That punk Irie, I can't forgive him.

108
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:28,140
Really.
How much does he have to toy with Kotoko until he is satisfied?

109
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:33,450
Well, actually Kotoko is the one
who is toying with her own feelings.

110
00:08:33,450 --> 00:08:36,040
But what about Kotoko's feelings?

111
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:39,190
She has been working so hard for him.

112
00:08:39,190 --> 00:08:42,580
But he's going to have an arranged
marriage meeting with another girl?

113
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:44,960
Kin-chan, you almost sound like...

114
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:49,920
you want Kotoko and Irie to be a couple.

115
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:52,590
That's not what I'm saying!

116
00:08:56,790 --> 00:09:01,670
I just want to see Kotoko smiling.

117
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:29,650
If I take over the company,

118
00:09:30,590 --> 00:09:33,580
all of the problems will be solved.

119
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:38,070
But your dream is to become a doctor, isn't it?

120
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:41,380
It's hasn't been long since I had that dream.

121
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:44,980
So you're going to give it up?

122
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,460
Irie-kun . . .

123
00:10:05,070 --> 00:10:07,390
At that moment, I felt like

124
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:11,650
our hearts were connected, but . . .

125
00:10:20,510 --> 00:10:24,380
Ah, I broke it.
Ouch.

126
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,460
Are you okay, Kotoko-chan?

127
00:10:26,490 --> 00:10:30,140
Oh no, you're bleeding!

128
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:35,270
It looks painful.

129
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:38,410
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

130
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,880
I'm sorry. I was spacing out.

131
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:45,020
It's because of Naoki's
arranged marriage meeting, isn't it?

132
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:47,260
I can't believe him.

133
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:52,960
But I still think you should be
Naoki's wife, Kotoko-chan.

134
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:56,150
Nevertheless, it's something that
Irie-kun has already decided on.

135
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:58,110
About that...

136
00:10:58,130 --> 00:11:03,200
No matter how I look at it, I just can't
believe he was telling us the truth.

137
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,850
About the company, too.

138
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:07,410
I admit that I was hoping

139
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:11,760
Naoki would take over Pandai.

140
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:15,740
But I've been watching him
working at the company...

141
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:19,260
I feel like something is wrong.

142
00:11:19,260 --> 00:11:24,960
I said to myself, "This is not what
Naoki really wants to do."

143
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:31,990
I think Naoki feels responsible for
the fact that my husband collapsed.

144
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:37,790
That's why he is sacrificing himself
and trying to save the company.

145
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:42,320
But do you think he would
go as far as getting married?
That's changing his life.

146
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:46,620
When he starts thinking about something,
he gets obsessed with the idea.

147
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,600
That's why...

148
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:57,080
I have a great idea.

149
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:00,390
A great idea?

150
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:18,790
I heard that Irie-kun is going to have
an arranged marriage meeting.

151
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:26,350
The girl is a granddaughter of the chairman
of a company named Hokueisha.

152
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:29,260
What? Chairman Oizumi's?

153
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,790
Do you know him?

154
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:32,120
Of course I do.

155
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:35,100
Don't you read the newspaper?

156
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:39,040
Chairman Oizumi is one of the big shots
of the financial world.

157
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:44,110
He has influence on many politicians.
He is the boss of the Japanese business world.

158
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:47,260
I didn't know it was the granddaughter
of such an important person.

159
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:52,630
Now that you mention it. I heard she has attended
Seishin Women's School since kindergarten.

160
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:54,610
I see.

161
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:57,100
She is a real princess, huh?

162
00:12:57,110 --> 00:13:02,270
Irie-kun said he liked her right away
when he saw a picture of her.

163
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:05,990
She must be beautiful.

164
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:10,030
I don't like it.

165
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:12,480
Right?

166
00:13:12,510 --> 00:13:16,650
Why does the perfect girl appear
out of nowhere to take Irie-kun?

167
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:18,310
I can't let her take him.

168
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:22,310
Well, Mrs. Irie might be able
to do something about this.

169
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:25,450
Hmm? Mrs. Irie?

170
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,460
What are you talking about?

171
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:30,270
Oh, me?

172
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:32,410
Oh, it's nothing! Nevermind!

173
00:13:32,410 --> 00:13:35,300
What do you mean "nothing?"
Hurry up and tell me.

174
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:38,240
I'm sorry, It's top secret...

175
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:42,670
that she has a plan to ruin the meeting.
Ah!

176
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,800
I see...

177
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:50,230
"Ruin the meeting," huh?

178
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:53,880
You two never change.

179
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,910
What is it?

180
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:58,450
But...

181
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:03,140
Only this time, I will join you.

182
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:05,070
What?

183
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:17,280
[The Day of the Arranged Marriage Meeting]

184
00:14:18,310 --> 00:14:20,170
This way, please.

185
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:33,810
Oh, Naoki-kun and Mrs. Irie.
I've been waiting for you.

186
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,420
We are sorry for making you wait.

187
00:14:35,420 --> 00:14:37,530
Please sit down.

188
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:42,700
I'm sorry for doing this when
Mr. Irie is in the hospital.

189
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:47,340
As for our side, only my
granddaughter and I are here, too.

190
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:50,790
We shall have a formal meeting
with her parents...

191
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:53,200
when Mr. Irie gets better.

192
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:56,160
On another day.

193
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:01,700
Oh my, I wonder if that day will ever come.

194
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:04,100
Mother!

195
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:07,930
One, two. One, two.

196
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:10,650
Why do we have to wear this?

197
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:16,750
We have no choice. This is the only way
that we wouldn't look suspicious in the garden.

198
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:19,530
Look, over there.

199
00:15:29,550 --> 00:15:31,240
Hmm

200
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:35,170
How does she look?
The granddaughter of Chairman Oizumi.

201
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:39,740
It looks like she is not there yet.

202
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,430
Wha is she doing?

203
00:15:41,430 --> 00:15:44,260
Sahoko is getting ready right now.

204
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,660
She will be here soon.

205
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:49,330
I'm sorry for being late.

206
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:51,830
Oh Sahoko, we've been
waiting for you.

207
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:53,740
Oh my.

208
00:16:04,010 --> 00:16:06,660
You are from...

209
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:15,470
Are you OK?

210
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:18,430
Do you remember me?

211
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:22,600
I never forget a beautiful lady.

212
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:26,110
Great, you two have met before.

213
00:16:26,110 --> 00:16:27,710
It's simple then.

214
00:16:27,710 --> 00:16:30,890
Sahoko, you should sit down.

215
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:45,840
Hey.

216
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:48,570
What are you doing?
You shouldn't space out.

217
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,620
Let me see.

218
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:05,260
Hmph, she might be pretty,
but she probably has no brains.

219
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:10,530
You are right! You are right!
Alright, let's get closer and
listen to their conversation!

220
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:19,040
Crawl and advance!
Let's go!

221
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:21,300
Are you serious?

222
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:28,200
I can't do this.

223
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:47,270
What is your hobby, Sahoko-san?

224
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:50,860
I'm not good at anything special.

225
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:55,250
I'm only good at cooking,
sewing and crafting.

226
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:57,130
very boring things.

227
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:59,530
Yes, indeed.

228
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:02,270
Boring.

229
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:08,410
Mrs. Irie, nice!

230
00:18:08,410 --> 00:18:11,020
Shh, they can hear you.

231
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:14,990
It's not something that
I should say, but...

232
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:17,690
Sahoko is quiet and perfect as a lady.

233
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:21,390
She is like a modern version of
an old traditional Japanese woman.

234
00:18:21,460 --> 00:18:24,640
Sounds very nice.
I like quiet women.

235
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:28,210
Wow, an "old traditional Japanese woman?"

236
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:31,360
So old.

237
00:18:31,430 --> 00:18:37,040
No wonder you seem like
you are missing your youth.

238
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:52,870
Um... Naoki-san,
what do you like to do?

239
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:55,090
Well...

240
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:57,290
I like to read books.

241
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:59,430
And I play tennis a little bit.

242
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:01,470
"A little bit?"

243
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:05,250
I've heard that you won many competitions.

244
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,340
That's amazing.

245
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:09,330
I can teach you next time.

246
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:11,170
-What?
-Huh?

247
00:19:11,170 --> 00:19:13,150
I'm glad to hear that.

248
00:19:13,150 --> 00:19:16,890
But I'm very bad, so you might get fed up with me.

249
00:19:16,930 --> 00:19:19,240
I'm sure he will be fed up.

250
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,850
Mother!

251
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:26,060
Well, my son, Naoki is very mean.

252
